ve a safe mobile trigger if needed. Use existing header or global layout mounting without redesigning the header or landing page. No API calls. Use premium modal/command UI inspired by modern command palettes and Aceternity-style effects if lightweight. Run lint/build.\"\n121 |   },\n122 |   {\n123 |     \"id\": \"15-frontend-only-placeholder-safety\",\n124 |     \"title\": \"Ensure frontend-only placeholders\",\n125 |     \"scope\": \"frontend-safety\",\n126 |     \"target\": \"forms and interactive tools\",\n127 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n128 |     \"prompt\": \"Audit and fix all forms and interactive tools to be frontend-only placeholders. Check Contact, Newsletter, Portal login, Control Center, Talk to Agent, Blueprint, Assessment, ROI, Sandbox, Proposal Builder, Marketplace, Foundry Studio. No real API calls, no auth, no AWS, no OTP sending, no real email sending, no database calls, no export file generation, no env dependency. If an existing legacy API route exists, do not use it from the public frontend. Placeholder copy must clearly say backend/FastAPI integration will come later only where appropriate. Run grep/search for fetch, axios, app/api calls, localhost, NEXT_PUBLIC_API, AWS, Cognito, SES, S3. Fix violations only. Run lint/build.\"\n129 |   },\n130 |   {\n131 |     \"id\": \"16-why-gff-ai-design-family\",\n132 |     \"title\": \"Design Why GFF AI page family\",\n133 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n134 |     \"target\": \"Why GFF AI explicit pages\",\n135 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n136 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /why-gff-ai and all Why GFF AI subpages into a premium executive narrative design family. Do not touch the landing page. Pages: /why-gff-ai, /why-gff-ai/mission, /why-gff-ai/vision, /why-gff-ai/garage-foundry-factory, /why-gff-ai/operating-model, /why-gff-ai/leadership, /why-gff-ai/global-model, /why-gff-ai/technology-philosophy, /why-gff-ai/differentiator. Design mood: strategic, editorial, boardroom-level, 